<table width="750" border="0" align="center">
  <tr>
    <td class="style_titleMax">Introduction</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td> <div>
      <div align="justify">
        <table width="700" border="1" align="center" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">
          <tr>
            <td class="style_field_data"><p align="justify"><strong>Background:</strong> Polymerase chain reaction with confronting two-pair primers (PCR-CTPP) is a time- and cost-effective SNP genotyping method that has the advantage of simplicity. In the recent years, there are many SNPs successfully genotyped by it. However, computation of feasible CTPP primers is still challenging.

</p>
              <div align="justify">
                <p><strong>Results: </strong> In this study, we propose a GA (genetic algorithm)-based method to design a feasible CTPP primer set for performing a reliable PCR experiment. The SLC6A4 gene with 288 SNPs were tested for dry dock experiments indicate that the proposed algorithm provides CTPP primers satisfied most primer constraints. One SNP rs12449783 in the SLC6A4 gene was taken as an example for the wet experiments using electrophoresis validate that the GA-based design method provides reliable CTPP primer sets for SNP genotyping. </p>
                <p><strong>Conclusions: </strong>The GA-based CTPP primer design method has serious melting temperature and all kind of common primer constraints estimation. It can assist the biologists and researchers to obtain a feasible CTTP primer set. The GA-CTPP program is implemented in JAVA and a user-friendly input interface is freely available at <a href="http://bio.kuas.edu.tw/ga-ctpp/">http://bio.kuas.edu.tw/ga-ctpp/</a>. </p>
                <p align="center"><img src="images/ga-ctpp/A.jpg" width="670" height="232"><br>
                (A) PCR-CTPP running in gel electrophoresis.</p>
                <p align="center"><img src="images/ga-ctpp/B.jpg" width="300" height="266"><br>
  (B) by TaqMan probe.</p>
                <p align="justify"> The SNP genotyping results of rs12449783 by (<strong>A</strong>) PCR-CTPP running in gel electrophoresis and (<strong>B</strong>) by TaqMan probe. (<strong>A</strong>) M and B indicate the 100 bp markers and blank, respectively. CC, AA, and AC indicate the control DNAs with known genotypes for CC, AA, and AC, respectively. The <em>Pf</em>1/<em>Pr</em>1 and <em>Pf</em>2/<em>Pr</em>2primer pairs are designed to specifically amplify the A- and C-containing alleles for genotypes AA and AC <em>vs.</em> genotypes CC and AC, respectively. The <em>Pf</em>1/<em>Pr</em>2 primer pair is designed to amplify the A- or C-containing alleles (CC, AA, and AC). </p>
              </div>
              </td>
          </tr>
        </table>
        </div>
